      "content": "While there isn't a straightforward way to measure the exact \"lie detection tone\" using standard instruments, researchers have explored various acoustic and physiological methods to detect deception. Some studies have used electroacoustic analysis and EEG to detect subtle changes in brain activity and vocalizations when people lie, often associated with increased stress and cognitive load. However, these methods are highly complex and not yet widely used in everyday applications.",
