      "content": "You're onto something there. Research suggests that the physical sensation of detecting a lie can't be solely attributed to cognitive load or emotional factors, as it tends to occur even when you're not consciously aware of those. Some studies have investigated the possibility of detecting deception through specific acoustic patterns, such as changes in vocal tract resonances or non-linear spectral features. However, the relationship between these patterns and the exact \"lie detection tone\" you described is still not well understood and requires further investigation.",
